# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Taqa — environment variables template
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file to a new file named  .env.local
#   2. Replace every "your-...-here" placeholder with the REAL value
#      (see the instructions Claude gave you for where to find each one).
#   3. Restart the dev server (Ctrl+C, then `npm run dev`) after editing.
#
# RULES:
#   - Variables that start with NEXT_PUBLIC_ are sent to the browser. Safe to expose.
#   - The other two (SERVICE_ROLE_KEY, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY) are SECRET. They must
#     ONLY ever be read on the server. Never put NEXT_PUBLIC_ in front of them.
#   - Never commit your real .env.local to git (it's already git-ignored).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Supabase (from your Supabase project dashboard) ---

# Project URL, e.g. https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your-supabase-project-url-here

# Public "anon" key (safe to expose to the browser)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key-here

# SECRET service-role key (full database access — server-side only, never exposed)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-supabase-service-role-key-here

# --- Anthropic (from the Anthropic Console) ---

# SECRET API key for calling Claude (server-side only)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-anthropic-api-key-here
